50|$|Survivors <b>basic</b> <b>pension</b> - The {{survivors}} <b>basic</b> <b>pension</b> {{is provided}} {{to family members}} (spouses who care for children, or dependent children themselves) of national pension members who pass away. The benefit amount is ¥1,020,000 (as of financial year 2010, for a wife with one child). For naturalized citizens of Japan, {{the period of time}} between April 1, 1964 and the day prior to them become citizens in which they lived overseas will be included in the 25 year qualifying period for the old age <b>basic</b> <b>pension.</b> However, this time will not be used in calculating the benefit they will receive.|$|E
