50|$|UK State <b>Pension.</b> The <b>Basic</b> State <b>Pension</b> {{is based}} on the National Insurance record of the individual. Each year that National Insurance was paid is called a {{qualifying}} year. Men born after 5 April 1945 and women born after 5 April 1950 need 30 qualifying years for a full <b>Basic</b> State <b>Pension,</b> with a single qualifying year required to get any State Pension. Men born before 6 April 1945 needed 44 qualifying years for a full <b>Basic</b> State <b>Pension,</b> and women born before 6 April 1950 needed 39 years; to get any State Pension, an individual needed 25 per cent of the qualifying years required for a full pension. Those who reach the state retirement age after 5 April 2016 need 35 qualifying years for a full pension.|$|R
